comments.body:
Deleted the existing `pdc-discovery-staging-1` collection and recreated it. The new one looks OK but the error message still displays at the top of the Solr home page. 

It is strange that the error message points to `replica_n3` when we only use a replication factor of two and therefore we only have `replica_n1` and `replica_n2` files. 

![Screenshot 2023-07-10 at 12 02 14 PM](https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_discovery/assets/568286/18d3e5a4-5612-4ac9-8a40-775fce4912df)

The error only shows on the homepage for `lib-solr-staging4`, the other two boxes (`lib-solr-staging5` and `lib-solr-staging6`) don't show the error. 

Given that there is no `replica3` in any of our collections and the error only shows on one box, I would like to restart `lib-solr-staging4` and see if the error goes away.

pulfalight.title: Update content icon in TOC to be grayed out if not direct

comments.body:
I tried messing with some icons that don't use colors to differentiate between direct and indirect online content. I'm not happy with the outcome, but here they are so everyone can review.  

![has_online_content_24x24](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/609368/a1725c5b-51bf-4707-8f3c-94fdcf213fa0)
![some_online_content-24x24](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/609368/1c938187-daa4-45c5-8e03-8779126caaee)
![some_online_content](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/609368/32565330-4ac5-45c0-b25e-c45b47faee99)
![has_online_content](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/609368/214e0c5f-f4f6-4378-b94c-cb48438a472a)

Also, it turns out that the green we use in the TOC does not pass the WCAG AA Accessibility guidelines for contrast. Green Hex Number #397339 is the lightest green that is AA acceptable at that text size with the current TOC background colors. In order to get the "breadcrumbing" effect we want, we should change the background of those that have direct online content to match the icon color. Here is a mockup of what that would look like using Green #397339: 

![pulfalight-accessible](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/609368/e609f77c-0a32-4180-b89c-b4f9898324df)

https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/tree/grayed-out-icons-w-bar has some CSS that should make some of these suggestions easier to implement.

![Screen Shot 2023-07-10 at 1 51 55 PM](https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/assets/2806645/dcde7e05-3518-4115-92cf-a15e58d5edc0)

is what that looks like right now.
